**INPUT.md defines the original product vision for agents-reverse-engineer as a brownfield documentation tool using Recursive Language Model (RLM) algorithm to generate AI assistant documentation through bottom-up directory traversal.**

## Vision Statement

Documents the inception rationale: streamlining brownfield project documentation to provide agents with clear codebase overviews, enabling easier long-term maintenance alongside complementary tools (SpecKit, BMAD, GSD).

## Core Feature Requirements

Specifies RLM execution pattern: build project structure tree, process leaf files first (generate `{filename}.sum` summaries), aggregate directory-level documentation recursively backward to root, produce `AGENTS.md` per directory with optional supplementary files (`ARCHITECTURE.md`, `STRUCTURE.md`, `STACK.md`, `INTEGRATIONS.md`, `INFRASTRUCTURE.md`, `CONVENTIONS.md`, `TESTING.md`, `PATTERNS.md`, `CONCERNS.md`).

## Multi-Platform Command Interface

Requires Claude Code command integration and equivalent alternatives for other LLM agent tools, with session-end hooks for incremental update of impacted files.

## Research Directive

Instructs detailed analysis of GSD and BMAD methodologies, focusing on brownfield project approaches, repository structure patterns, special commands, and codebase implementation details to inform ARE's architecture.

## Usage Examples

Demonstrates two primary commands: `/are-generate` (full documentation generation) and `/are-update` (incremental updates).

## Relationship to Implementation

This specification document preceded implementation of the three-phase pipeline (`src/generation/orchestrator.ts`), post-order directory traversal (`getAffectedDirectories()`, depth-based sorting), file summary generation (`.sum` files via `writeSumFile()`), directory aggregation (`AGENTS.md` via `writeAgentsMd()`), and root document synthesis (`CLAUDE.md`, `GEMINI.md`, `OPENCODE.md` via `src/integration/generate.ts`).